<subSubSection id="E9B4778E66DEB11CC278CE325D941FA4" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="A7A53B9FF568FC4B7063C5666EFBB729" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
81. 
<taxonomicName id="A37EF8E56A3C02A36252E223C51644AB" LSID="A34FF62A-89C3-5273-A4E0-C4CB5AA9C4BF" authority="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 54. 1792. (Desrousseaux. 1792: 541)." authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 54. 1792. (Desrousseaux. 1792: 541)." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus fruticulosus" order="Solanales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticulosus">Convolvulus fruticulosus Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.]3: 54. 1792. (Desrousseaux. 1792: 541).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DA645AA994878C449730F0E401667AA7" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="type">
<paragraph id="F21A2FD975B8F95529530F3DDB5B9FFF" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED366A020C0B8485A4CA10F8CBD5D181" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">CANARY ISLANDS, a plant grown at Paris from seed sent by Collignon from the Canary Islands (holotype P [Herb. Lam.]!).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D7EC883E291F4145BC670FD2FCDA5B5" lastPageId="110" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph id="F1167B0553F573D7DBA2A1B60BD6FC08" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F142EB2DA6A5095B01B28F963CEE93E9" lastPageId="110" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
Woody-based scrambling plant with long trailing stems to 1.5 m. Leaves shortly petiolate, 1-5 
<normalizedToken id="83E438B669AEB4F8432564C382DD8E4A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1.4(-2.5) cm, oblong, apiculate, entire, base sub 
<pageBreakToken id="E8837F1C0E6B67740DC462EFE00BCE9B" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" start="start">cordate</pageBreakToken>
, weakly auriculate, thinly to densely tomentellous on both surfaces; petioles 2-4 mm. Flowers 1-3 in shortly pedunculate, axillary cymes the flowers and leaves crowded together; peduncles 0-10 mm; bracteoles, 5-6 mm, filiform, caducous; pedicels 5-12 mm; sepals 6-7 (-9) 
<normalizedToken id="FEA4A4E8D1B3D39F641FD17FCE5DA743" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 mm, pubescent, outer sepals broadly oblong-elliptic, obtuse to subacute, inner sepals oblong, acute to mucronate; corolla 1.5-1.7 cm long, pale blue, weakly lobed, midpetaline bands pilose; filaments glandular, ovary 3.5 mm long, pilose at apex or glabrous; style glabrous except sometimes near the base, divided 3 mm above base; stigmas 3 mm. Capsule globose-conical, apiculate, c. 4-8 mm long, pilose apically or glabrous; seeds tuberculate, glabrous. [
<bibRefCitation id="A0D2AC937090070F6C2C4B7D5B7CC532" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="E7530348C548B5D061B60199FD2CE733" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 250, 
<bibRefCitation id="CEE523BBA5B38C5D996F4363F782D167" author="Bramwell, D" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Egypt" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" refId="B60" refString="Bramwell, D, Bramwell, Z, 2001. Wild flowers of the Canary Islands (2nd ed.). Rueda, Madrid, 1-437." title="Wild flowers of the Canary Islands (2 nd ed.). Rueda, Madrid, 1 - 437." year="2001">Bramwell and Bramwell 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 262-263 (photo); 
<bibRefCitation id="EBAAEFE35AF488BFF1D1026D7DCB0555" author="Schoenfelder, P" journalOrPublisher="Kosmos, Stuttgart" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 319" refId="B322" refString="Schoenfelder, P, Schoenfelder, I, 1997. Die Kosmos Kanarenflora. Kosmos, Stuttgart: 1 - 319" title="Die Kosmos Kanarenflora" year="1997">
<normalizedToken id="D8CC726FC3DD2B7007C1635B64E22DAD" originalValue="Schönfelder">Schoenfelder</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="53F54478BC064320231A7EB9D3159D3A" originalValue="Schönfelder">Schoenfelder</normalizedToken>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
: 176-177 (photo)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="717C2BBDA2109AF8776ECDD3E9A5D344" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="notes">
<paragraph id="5EA84DD7B692C891999B6BDBCD115409" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35521787C49AC83D0B1460BB1182FAC" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="9540F6885DD8976374335ADECA6EB4BB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus fruticulosus" order="Solanales" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fruticulosus">
<emphasis id="2CE13701C182C07D7186AFD462082956" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Convolvulus fruticulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very variable species endemic to the Canary Islands, and populations appear to vary from island to island and from one part of an island to another part. Populations on the smaller islands are poorly known. Variation is mostly in indumentum, shape of the leaf base, development of the inflorescence and sepal shape. These differences do not correlate well with each other and the various names cited in the synonymy below seem to have been applied somewhat arbitrarily to one variant or another. As sepal shape is commonly of significance in taxon delimitation in 
<taxonomicName id="E548300518B305DA011FD36FEA631B28" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus" order="Solanales" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A80AF8C40FA6A172CEBB2531C94C6E90" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Convolvulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, our infraspecific classification is based primarily on this character as was 
<bibRefCitation id="FDC27DDF0CCE8A0EE341B74052EBF142" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="D8E313CB7A93B85E520F0AE9EC4D9FAE" originalValue="Sa’ad’s">Sa'ad's</normalizedToken>
(1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 251-252) but we disagree on the decisive sepal characters and on the interpretation or assignation of the various names. We recognise two subspecies:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
